# Places API routes (`src/app/api/places`)

## Keys

- Server routes read `process.env.GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY ?? process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`.
- Prefer a dedicated **server** key in production (Vercel: `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`); browser map uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` with referrer restrictions.

## Google usage

- Nearby search uses **Places API (New)** — `POST https://places.googleapis.com/v1/places:searchText` with `X-Goog-Api-Key` and `X-Goog-FieldMask`. Do not reintroduce legacy `nearbysearch` / `textsearch` JSON endpoints.
- Geocode uses `https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json`; suggest uses legacy Place Autocomplete JSON when the key is present.
- On failure, preserve Nominatim fallbacks and clear JSON error messages for the client where applicable.

## Debugging

- Health check: `GET /api/places/health` (optional `?probe=false` to skip live probes). Use it to verify which key is active and which Google surface returns errors.
